main event: Two bright lights were observed in Wyoming, Ohio on May 1, 1968 at 9:15 PM. The lights were initially stationary, then slowly moved eastward.
interesting points: The lights were bright and stationary at first, then moved slowly eastward.
The sighting lasted for approximately 10 minutes.
The weather conditions were clear with no clouds.
No other observers were listed in the report.
The investigator found no further information about the sighting.
